  "title": "Direct Debit Mandate",
  "description": "An agreement between a debtor and a creditor allowing the creditor to instruct the bank to debit the debtors account\r\n\r\nAuthorization in favour of the creditor given by the debtor to debit its own account. (ISO20022)\r\n\r\nA mandate that the (corporate) customer signs with its customers (consumer and business). \r\n\r\nA financial arrangement that allows one party, typically an organization or business, to collect payments from another party, usually a customer or client, directly from their bank account. It's a convenient and automated method of making recurring payments, such as monthly bills, subscriptions, memberships, and other regular expenses.",
